# Lab / compose: Kitchen API → Jupiter operator control plane (DV-077 / DV-072)
# Copy into your .env next to docker-compose and set values for your Jupiter host.
#
# KITCHEN_JUPITER_CONTROL_BASE — BlackBox api → Sean Jupiter HTTP (GET/POST policy).
#
# Use the SAME scheme + host + port the operator uses in the browser (your real hostname).
# Example (replace with your real host): http://YOUR-JUPITER-HOST:707
# DNS should resolve that name to the same Jupiter process as any internal hostname; this
# file does not configure DNS — only the URL Kitchen uses for server-to-server calls.
#
# Login page vs API:
# - Opening /dashboard in a browser requires operator login (session) — normal.
# - Kitchen and curl use the JSON API with Bearer, not the browser cookie, e.g.:
#   curl -sk -H "Authorization: Bearer $KITCHEN_JUPITER_OPERATOR_TOKEN" \
#     "$KITCHEN_JUPITER_CONTROL_BASE/api/v1/jupiter/policy"
#
# Wrong host (e.g. http://127.0.0.1:8080) = BlackBox api, not Sean — policy mismatch.
KITCHEN_JUPITER_CONTROL_BASE=
# Token must match Sean's JUPITER_OPERATOR_TOKEN (same as Kitchen → Jupiter POST Bearer).
KITCHEN_JUPITER_OPERATOR_TOKEN=
